trans-unit.source: List Admin Keys (Azure Search Management REST API)
trans-unit.target: List Admin Keys (Azure Search Management REST API)

trans-unit.source: The <languageKeyword>List Admin Keys</languageKeyword> operation returns the primary and secondary admin keys for the specified Search service.
trans-unit.target: The <languageKeyword>List Admin Keys</languageKeyword> operation returns the primary and secondary admin keys for the specified Search service.

trans-unit.source: The POST method is used because this action returns read-write keys.
trans-unit.target: The POST method is used because this action returns read-write keys.

trans-unit.source: Admin keys are created with the service.
trans-unit.target: Admin keys are created with the service.

trans-unit.source: There are always two keys, primary and secondary.
trans-unit.target: There are always two keys, primary and secondary.

trans-unit.source: You can regenerate these keys, but you cannot delete them.
trans-unit.target: You can regenerate these keys, but you cannot delete them.
